        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 6:16PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 616 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Yosemite Valley, or 19 miles west of June Lake, moving
south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Merced Lake High Sierra Camp, Vogelsang High Sierra Camp, Sunrise
High Sierra Camp, Little Yosemite Valley Campground, Merced Lake
Ranger Station, Little Yosemite Valley Ranger Station, Morraine Dome
Campground, and Tenaya Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
